🧠 Using Generative AI – Quick Summary

Generative AI creates new content like text, images, videos, and code.

🔑 4 Main Uses
- Create: Generate content (emails, images, videos, code).
- Summarize: Turn large information into short, useful insights.
- Discover: Find information, patterns, and insights quickly.
- Automate: Handle repetitive tasks (documentation, analysis, alerts).

⚡ Multimodal Capability
- Works across text, images, audio, video, PDFs—even combining them.

🎯 Business Impact
- Improves productivity, decision-making, creativity, and efficiency
- Reduces manual effort and operational costs

🧠 Multimodal Generative AI – Summary
- Multimodal GenAI can process and combine multiple data types (text, images, audio, video), giving a richer understanding of complex workflows.
- It helps solve real-world business problems where information exists in different formats, not just text.

🚗 Example (Automotive)
- A virtual assistant uses:
- Gemini → to understand user queries and interact conversationally
- Vertex AI Search → to retrieve relevant info from manuals, videos, FAQs

Users can:
- Ask questions naturally
- Upload images (e.g., warning light)
- Get step-by-step troubleshooting guidance

🎯 Benefits
- Faster problem resolution
- Reduced customer support costs
- Improved efficiency and user experience
- Better accessibility for non-technical users

🧠 How Generative AI Works (Foundation Models)
- Foundation models are large AI models trained on massive, diverse datasets (text, images, code, etc.).
- They form the core of generative AI, enabling systems to handle many different tasks.

🔑 Key Concepts
- AI: Machines performing human-like tasks (e.g., understanding language).
- ML: Systems learn from data to solve problems.
- Foundation models: Unlike traditional AI, they are general-purpose, not task-specific.
- LLMs: A type of foundation model focused on language.

⚙️ Key Features
- Trained on diverse data → learns broad patterns
- Flexible → one model, many use cases
- Adaptable → can be fine-tuned for specific needs

📌 Examples
- Gemini: Multimodal (text, images, video, code) → supports many tasks
- Imagen: Focused on image generation from text

