🧠 GenAI Strategy (Top-Down + Bottom-Up) – Summary
- Organizations should adopt GenAI with a clear strategy, not blindly.
- 
🔄 Two-Fold Approach
- Top-down (Leadership):
- Define vision and align GenAI with business goals
- Prioritize high-impact use cases
- Provide resources and governance
- Bottom-up (Teams):
- Encourage employees to experiment and share ideas
- Identify practical, real-world use cases
- Drive innovation from day-to-day work

⚙️ Key Success Factors
- Focus on high-value, feasible use cases
- Promote experimentation and learning
- Ensure responsible AI usage
- Allocate proper resources
- Measure impact and ROI
- Continuously improve and iterate

💡 Brainstorming GenAI Use Cases – Summary
- Use a Creative Matrix to systematically generate ideas.

⚙️ How it works
- Create two axes:
- Axis 1 → GenAI capabilities (tools, modalities, products)
- Axis 2 → Business aspects (workflows, goals, personas)
- Brainstorm ideas at each intersection (like sticky notes)

🧠 Examples
- Image search tool for product discovery
- AI chatbot for customer support
- Predictive analytics for demand forecasting

🎯 Next Step: Prioritization
- Evaluate ideas based on:
- Impact (value)
- Feasibility (effort, cost)

🧠 Humans + GenAI (Augmentation vs Automation) – Summary
🔑 Core Idea
- GenAI should support humans, not replace them
- Shift from doing tasks → strategic thinking
  
⚖️ Augmentation (Enhancing Humans)
- Use GenAI to assist in:
- Critical thinking & decision-making
- Creativity & innovation
- Collaboration & relationships
- Strategic planning & vision

👉 Humans remain essential for judgment and direction.

⚙️ Automation (Replacing Tasks)
- Use GenAI for:
- Repetitive, rule-based tasks (data entry, basic coding)
- Time-consuming work (research, summarization, drafts)

👥 Human-in-the-Loop (Always Needed)
- Data selection & quality control
- Prompt design
- Output review & refinement
- Continuous feedback & improvement

🧪 Examples
- Chatbot answering FAQs → Automation
- Analyst using AI insights for decisions → Augmentation
- AI generating product descriptions → Automation
- AI-assisted coding with human review → Augmentation
  
